    <title>Preview Bond Rendering</title>
    
    <section title="New Bond Rendering options">

<table border="1">
<tr>
<td>
<h1>aspirin</h1>
    <appletExample>
    <![CDATA[
<applet name="jmol" code="JmolApplet" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
        width="400" height="400" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="emulate"   value="chime" />
  <param name="load"      value="aspirina.mol.gz" />
</applet>]]>
    </appletExample>
</td>

<td>
If you use &lt;param name='emulate' value='chime' /&gt; then the default
representation is wireframe bonds on a black background. For
compatibility with the RasMol scripting language, the command to control
bondsize is called <b>wireframe</b>. Try the following: <br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="wireframe 0.1" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="wireframe 0.1" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="wireframe 0.125" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="wireframe 0.125" />
</applet><br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="wireframe 0.25" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="wireframe 0.25" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="wireframe 0.5" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="wireframe 0.5" />
</applet><br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="wireframe on" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="wireframe on" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="wireframe off" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="wireframe off" />
</applet><br />
For compatibility with existing RasMol/Chime scripts, multiple bonds are not
displayed with larger bonds. <i>(In the future jmol will give the user explicit
control over this behavior by introducing another script command.)</i>
<p />

By default, a bond inherits the colors of the two atoms it connects. 
If you want to change the bond color you can assign explic colors <br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="color bonds dodgerblue" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="color bonds dodgerblue" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="color bonds goldenrod" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="color bonds goldenrod" />
</applet><br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="color bonds limegreen" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="color bonds limegreen" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="color bonds none" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="color bonds none" />
</applet> <br />
Script commands operate on the currently selected set of <b>atoms</b>.
Bonds are selected based upon on the <i>bondmode</i>.
The default bondmode is <i>and</i>. Both atoms must be selected in
order for the script mode to affect the bond. If you switch the bondmode
to <i>or</i> then the bond will be affected if either atom is selected.
Try combinations of these buttons with the script commands above.<br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="set bondmode and" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="set bondmode and" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="set bondmode or" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="set bondmode or" />
</applet><br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="select carbon" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="select carbon" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="select oxygen" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="select oxygen" />
</applet><br />
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="select hydrogen" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="select hydrogen" />
</applet>
<applet code="JmolAppletControl" archive="head/JmolApplet.jar"
  height="20" width="200" mayscript="true" >
  <param name="type"  value="button" />
  <param name="label"  value="select all" />
  <param name="target" value="jmol" />
  <param name="script" value="select all" />
</applet> <br />

</td>

